{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fc40337e-1cee-49ed-b1ad-1d93f58be231","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. Here are the main approaches:\n\n### Using `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\n# Install the tool\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Analyze the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n### Using LLDB (Linux)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-sos\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\nThen use `clrstack`, `pe`, `dso`, etc.\n\n### Quick triage steps\n1. Run `pe` first to see if there's an unhandled exception\n2. Run `clrstack` to see where execution was at crash time\n3. Run `threads` to check for deadlocks or other suspicious thread states\n\nWould you like help running any of these commands on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"af006526-e957-488b-93a5-7210a19071f1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description says it's for collecting/configuring crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. It explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo I should NOT invoke that skill. Instead, I'll provide guidance directly.","outputTokens":400,"requestId":"7848:1E3500:1FF745C:2384876:69FA9F2B"},"id":"1ac1b025-aec1-46d3-9e4e-98130da68b48","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:53:58.268Z","parentId":"f032d9bb-7ed7-4a62-b441-c391a896dc83"}
